<h1>Typefaces</h1>

<p>
  The HTML renderer bundles three font variants — Noto Sans, Noto Serif, and
  PetalumaScript (a handwritten Real Book style) — so charts have a consistent
  house style wherever they appear, with no network dependency. You can also override the font entirely using the
  <code>--grigson-font-family</code> CSS custom property, which lets you bring
  any typeface you like.
</p>
<p>
  Below, the same "Autumn Leaves" chart is rendered three ways. Notice how the
  lining figures in the Noto fonts keep chord extensions (7, 9, 11…) sitting
  neatly on the baseline, unlike the old Georgia default where digits like 3, 4,
  5, 7, 9 dipped below it.
</p>

<div class="typeface-examples">

  <section>
    <h2>Sans-serif (default)</h2>
    <p>Noto Sans — the default when no <code>typeface</code> attribute is set.</p>
    <grigson-chart normalise>
      <template>{{ 'autumn-leaves' | readChart }}</template>
    </grigson-chart>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Serif</h2>
    <p>Noto Serif — set <code>typeface="serif"</code> on <code>&lt;grigson-html-renderer&gt;</code>.</p>
    <grigson-chart normalise>
      <grigson-html-renderer typeface="serif"></grigson-html-renderer>
      <template>{{ 'autumn-leaves' | readChart }}</template>
    </grigson-chart>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Cursive</h2>
    <p>Petaluma — set <code>typeface="petaluma"</code> on <code>&lt;grigson-html-renderer&gt;</code>.</p>
    <grigson-chart normalise>
      <grigson-html-renderer notation-preset="realbook" typeface="cursive"></grigson-html-renderer>
      <template>{{ 'autumn-leaves' | readChart }}</template>
    </grigson-chart>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Finale Jazz</h2>
    <p>
      A jazz handwriting style derived from the OFL-licensed Finale Jazz font by MakeMusic,
      loaded from jsDelivr and applied via <code>--grigson-font-family</code> on the
      <code>&lt;grigson-chart&gt;</code> element.
    </p>
    <grigson-chart normalise style="--grigson-font-family: 'FinaleJazz', cursive; --grigson-time-sig-font-size: 1em; --grigson-time-sig-top: 30%;  --grigson-time-sig-line-height: 0.7;">
      <grigson-html-renderer notation-preset="realbook"></grigson-html-renderer>
      <template>{{ 'autumn-leaves' | readChart }}</template>
    </grigson-chart>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Kaushan Script</h2>
    <p>
      An external display font loaded from Google Fonts, applied via
      <code>--grigson-font-family</code> on the <code>&lt;grigson-chart&gt;</code> element.
      The Real Book notation preset is used here to avoid the △ character,
      which this font does not cover.
    </p>
    <grigson-chart normalise style="--grigson-font-family: 'Kaushan Script', cursive;">
      <grigson-html-renderer notation-preset="realbook" accidentals="ascii"></grigson-html-renderer>
      <template>{{ 'autumn-leaves' | readChart }}</template>
    </grigson-chart>
  </section>

</div>

